did.head: DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY

did.abstract: Student scrapbooks, with annotations, compiled by students in Professor Carol Kammen's History 126 course, documenting the freshman experience for the Classes of 1998, 1999, 2000, 2001, 2002, 2003, 2004, 2005, 2006, and 2007.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Student scrapbooks, with annotations, compiled by students in Professor Carol Kammen's History 126 course, documenting the freshman experience for the Classes of 1998, 1999, 2000, 2001, 2002, 2003, 2004, 2005, 2006, and 2007 relating to dormitory life, athletics, religious activities, fraternity and sorority rushing, academic life, social events and activities, college costs, food, letters to and from home, and other events characterizing the lives of new college students. Some scrapbooks include critiques by other members of the compiler's class.
